    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
        <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">How do I choose between a disc stack and decanter centrifuge?</summary>
        <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">The primary decision factors are: (1) <strong>Solids content</strong> — disc stack centrifuges handle &lt;2% solids; decanters handle up to 40%; (2) <strong>Particle size</strong> — disc stacks separate particles down to 0.5 microns; decanters handle &gt;100 microns; (3) <strong>Separation type</strong> — disc stacks excel at liquid-liquid separation (oil/water); decanters excel at solid-liquid separation (sludge dewatering).</p>
      </details>
      <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
        <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">What information do I need to select the right centrifuge size?</summary>
        <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">To select the right centrifuge: (1) Required throughput in GPM; (2) Fluid type and viscosity at operating temperature; (3) Percent solids in the feed; (4) Solid particle size distribution; (5) Desired separation quality. Dolphin Centrifuge engineers can size the right unit based on these parameters — call <a href="tel:+12485222573">(248) 522-2573</a>.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
        <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">Can centrifuge sample testing help select the right unit?</summary>
        <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">Yes. Dolphin Centrifuge offers free sample testing — send a fluid sample to our Warren, MI facility and our engineers will test it on our centrifuge equipment to characterize separation performance, determine the right centrifuge type, and size the appropriate model. This removes guesswork from centrifuge selection.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
        <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">What is the smallest disc stack centrifuge Dolphin Centrifuge supplies?</summary>
        <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">The smallest disc stack centrifuge system in Dolphin's lineup is the DMPX-010, rated at 7 GPM on diesel and 4 GPM on lube oil. For manual-clean disc centrifuges, the smallest is the DMB-004, rated at 4 GPM on diesel. Both are available as complete turnkey system modules.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5">
        <summary class="font-semibold text-navy cursor-pointer">What is the largest centrifuge Dolphin Centrifuge supplies?</summary>
        <p class="text-text-light mt-3 text-sm">For disc stack centrifuges, the largest standard system is the DMPX-070, rated at 59–72 GPM on diesel and 30–38 GPM on lube oil. For decanter centrifuges, the Alfa Laval NX-428 handles flow rates up to 80+ GPM. Multiple units can be installed in parallel for higher throughput requirements.</p>
      </details>
    </div>

